title: In Tennessee, Bush scores another game day in his SEC tour
text: Photo: Wade Payne, AP Republican presidential candidate and former Florida Gov. Jeb Bush signs an autograph as he attends a tailgate party before an NCAA college football game between Tennessee and Georgia Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015, in Knoxville, Tenn. Republican presidential candidate and former Florida Gov. Jeb Bush... KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (AP) — Jeb Bush is getting a jump on the so-called SEC primary by visiting the University of Tennessee and other campuses in Southern states that vote for the GOP's presidential nominee on March 1.
